reviewText: It is funny and even a bit thought provoking.  Ellen Barkin is fantastic!!  She has got the man in a woman's body down pat.  Jummy Smits is also wonderful as the best friend and lover want to be.....I love this movie every time I watch it, and I have watched it many times!!
summary: This movie is a favorite of mine
Title: Switch

reviewText: Switch is a great lesson in understanding the joys of being a male and female. all learned by a former MCP  when he is murdered and reincarnates as a woman.The choices given my Diety  and the temptations of a Devil are all played out. a wonderful video and a training film for those who are trying to understand Soul evolution and karma.Highly enjoyable, incredibly on-target and very insightful !  You will totally enjoy !
summary: Have your cake and eat it too !
Title: Switch

reviewText: If you want to laugh until you cry this is the movie. It kind of reminds me of Heaven can wait, but this one is absolutely out of the box funny.
Title: Switch

reviewText: Ellen Barkin plays the reincarnation of a murdered man.  Murdered by a trio of women who were fed up with his male chauvinistic ways.  Too bad for Heaven, too good for Hell he is sent back due to how he treated women, but, the devil (Bruce Payne) thinks it unfair and turns him into a her!  Coupled with the aid of the woman (Jobeth Williams) who murdered him and his best buddy (Jimmy Smits) this Man in a woman's body has to find one woman who likes him.  Barkin really succeeded at playing the role.  LOTS of noted people in it.  It is subtitled in English for the deaf.
Title: Switch

reviewText: Long before the flurry of slapstick, role-switching movies; daughter-mother, father-son, "Switch" paved the way with a serious look at changes and consequences.  A misogynist womanizing man dies (no spoilers), returns to life as a woman, and has to deal not only with a completely new role for "her"self, but must deal with the disaster (s)He left behind prior to his demise.  Ellen Barkin is perfect in her portrayal of a man in a new skin, and though her performance alone is worth the price of the movie, the story is well done and makes this movie an underrated diamond in a coal bin.  Definitely one you'll watch more than once.
Title: Switch
